#Filter for earthquakes
earthquake_mask = seismic_data['type'] == 'earthquake'
earthquake_data = seismic_data[earthquake_mask]

#Seismic dataframe to geodataframe converting longitude and latidude to point (geometry object) only for earthquakes
earthquakes = gpd.GeoDataFrame(earthquake_data, geometry=gpd.points_from_xy(earthquake_data.longitude, earthquake_data.latitude))

#Tectonic plate boundaries as a geopandas dataframe
plates_path = "plate-boundaries/doc.kml"
plates = gpd.read_file(plates_path, driver="KML")

#World as a geopandas data frame
world = gpd.read_file(gpd.datasets.get_path('naturalearth_lowres'))

#Initialise figure (create empty figure)
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 1, figsize=(30,30))

#Plots the world from the geodataframe (plots the geometry column by default)
world.plot(ax=ax, color='white', edgecolor = 'black')

#Plots the earthquakes from the geodataframe
earthquakes.plot(ax=ax, column=earthquakes['mag'], cmap="OrRd", marker='.', legend=True, legend_kwds={'shrink': 0.3, 'label': "Magnitude (Richter scale)"})

# Creates array of uniques plate names, creates random list of colors, loops over geodataframe plotting each platename a different random colour
plate_names = plates.Name.unique()
rand_color_list = [ "#%06x" % random.randint(0, 0xFFFFFF) for color in range(len(plate_names))]
for index, plate in enumerate(plate_names):
    mask = plates['Name'] == plate
    plates[mask].plot(ax=ax, color=rand_color_list[index])

#Customisation of the plot
plt.xlabel("Longitude (degree)")
plt.ylabel("Latitude (degree)")
plt.title('Plot of earthquakes and tectonic plates across the globe from {} to {}'.format(first_date, last_date), fontsize=25)

#Function which asks the user which continent they would like to map, along with the tectonic plates and earthquakes
def earthquake_map_by_continent(world, earthquakes, plates):
    continent_names = world.continent.unique() #Lists the unique continent names
    continent_number = input("Input the number correspnding to the continent you'd like to map {}".format(list(enumerate(continent_names)))) # Enumerates the continents and asks user which continent to select
    continent_selected = continent_names[int(continent_number)]
    continent_gdf = world[world.continent == continent_selected]
    aoi_bounds = continent_gdf.geometry.total_bounds #Find the bounds of the contintent (long and lat)
    xmin, ymin, xmax, ymax = aoi_bounds

    #Plot customisation
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,1, figsize = (10,10))
    ax.set_xlim([xmin, xmax])
    ax.set_ylim([ymin, ymax])
    ax.set_xlabel('Longitude (Degrees)')
    ax.set_ylabel('Latitude (Degrees)')
    ax.set_title("Plot of earthquakes in {} over the last 30 days".format(continent_selected))
    #Plots the earthquakes, continent and tectonic plates
    continent_gdf.plot(ax=ax, color='white', edgecolor = 'black')
    earthquakes.plot(ax=ax, column=earthquakes['mag'], cmap="OrRd", marker='.', legend=True, legend_kwds={'shrink': 0.3, 'label': "Magnitude (Richter scale)"})
    plates.plot(ax=ax, color='blue')



earthquake_map_by_continent(world, earthquakes, plates)

fig, axs = plt.subplots(2,2)
fig.set_size_inches(18.5, 10.5)

#Subplot 1 scatter graph of magnitude against depth
axs[0, 0].scatter(earthquakes['depth'], earthquakes['mag'], marker='.')
axs[0, 0].set_title('Magnitude of earthquakes against depth (past 30 days)')
axs[0, 0].set_xlabel('Depth (m)')
axs[0, 0].set_ylabel('Magnitude')

#Subplot 2 histogram of magnitude
axs[0, 1].hist(earthquakes['mag'], color='grey')
axs[0, 1].set_title('Histogram of earthquake magnitudes (past 30 days, red line=mean)')
axs[0, 1].set_xlabel('Magnitude')
axs[0, 1].set_ylabel('Count')
axs[0, 1].axvline(earthquakes['mag'].mean(), ls='--', color='red')

#Subplot 3 bar chart of algorithims
magtype_count = earthquakes.groupby(['magType']).size().reset_index()
magtype_count.columns = ['Algorithim', 'Count']
axs[1, 1].bar(magtype_count['Algorithim'], magtype_count['Count'], color='green')
axs[1, 1].set_title('Bar chart of magnitude algorithims used (past 30 days, red line=mean)')
axs[1, 1].set_xlabel('Magnitude Algorithim')
axs[1, 1].set_ylabel('Count')

#Subplot 4 hexagonal bin plot
axs[1, 0].hexbin(earthquakes['longitude'], earthquakes['latitude'], C=earthquakes['mag'], gridsize=(30,30), bins=20, cmap=plt.cm.Purples_r)
axs[1, 0].set_title('Hexbin plot of earthquakes (colored by cumulative magnitude, past 30 days)')
axs[1, 0].set_xlabel('Longitude')
axs[1, 0].set_ylabel('Latitude')
